    <node id="n18">
      <data key="d5"/>
      <data key="d6">
        <y:GenericNode configuration="com.yworks.flowchart.process">
          <y:Geometry height="186.75" width="624.640625" x="-2673.9486523437504" y="1058.7841145833283"/>
          <y:Fill color="#E8EEF7" color2="#FF9900" transparent="false"/>
          <y:BorderStyle color="#000000" type="line" width="1.0"/>
          <y:NodeLabel alignment="left" autoSizePolicy="content" fontFamily="Dialog" fontSize="12" fontStyle="plain" hasBackgroundColor="false" hasLineColor="false" height="165.712890625" horizontalTextPosition="center" iconTextGap="4" modelName="custom" textColor="#000000" verticalTextPosition="bottom" visible="true" width="584.98046875" x="19.830078125" xml:space="preserve" y="10.5185546875">Detection of humans based on number of detected Bluetooth beacons divides distance to 3 ranges. 
Detection changes in object distance ranges happens only after seconds. 
This is a very long duration for typical vehicle driving scenarios, this input cue is useful 
to setup an alertness level for the ADI function.

Definition of a threshold for the number of beacons in near field across alertness levels should 

In order to derive a more reliable alertness level, beacons from the devices inside the car can be disregarded:
- immediate distance range &lt;50cm can be disregarded
- near (50cm &lt; x &lt; 2/5m) and far (2/5m &lt; x &lt; 30/50m) distance range can be used with a weighted sum 
mapped onto different levels of alertness.<y:LabelModel><y:SmartNodeLabelModel distance="4.0"/></y:LabelModel><y:ModelParameter><y:SmartNodeLabelModelParameter labelRatioX="0.0" labelRatioY="0.0" nodeRatioX="0.0" nodeRatioY="0.0" offsetX="0.0" offsetY="0.0" upX="0.0" upY="-1.0"/></y:ModelParameter></y:NodeLabel>
        </y:GenericNode>
      </data>
    </node>
    <node id="n19">
      <data key="d5"/>
      <data key="d6">
        <y:GenericNode configuration="com.yworks.flowchart.process">
          <y:Geometry height="186.75" width="624.640625" x="2143.2070312499986" y="-1160.9375"/>
          <y:Fill color="#E8EEF7" color2="#B7C9E3" transparent="false"/>
          <y:BorderStyle color="#000000" type="line" width="1.0"/>
          <y:NodeLabel alignment="center" autoSizePolicy="content" fontFamily="Dialog" fontSize="12" fontStyle="plain" hasBackgroundColor="false" hasLineColor="false" height="136.310546875" horizontalTextPosition="center" iconTextGap="4" modelName="custom" textColor="#000000" verticalTextPosition="bottom" visible="true" width="523.615234375" x="50.5126953125" xml:space="preserve" y="25.2197265625">Detection of humans 
based on number of UWB devices useful for in setup of alertness level

Some SmartPhones also use UWB for precision positioning/navigation although not too common. 

Also cars use this for keyless entry as it eliminates relay attacks, and as parking radar

location accuracy: 0.1-0.5m
range: 10-200m<y:LabelModel><y:SmartNodeLabelModel distance="4.0"/></y:LabelModel><y:ModelParameter><y:SmartNodeLabelModelParameter labelRatioX="0.0" labelRatioY="0.0" nodeRatioX="0.0" nodeRatioY="0.0" offsetX="0.0" offsetY="0.0" upX="0.0" upY="-1.0"/></y:ModelParameter></y:NodeLabel>
