          <y:BorderStyle color="#000000" type="line" width="1.0"/>
          <y:NodeLabel alignment="center" autoSizePolicy="content" fontFamily="Dialog" fontSize="12" fontStyle="plain" hasBackgroundColor="false" hasLineColor="false" height="33.40234375" horizontalTextPosition="center" iconTextGap="4" modelName="custom" textColor="#000000" verticalTextPosition="bottom" visible="true" width="130.732421875" x="50.6337890625" xml:space="preserve" y="3.298828125">&lt;&lt;ProvidedPort&gt;&gt;
AccelerationRawValues<y:LabelModel><y:SmartNodeLabelModel distance="4.0"/></y:LabelModel><y:ModelParameter><y:SmartNodeLabelModelParameter labelRatioX="0.0" labelRatioY="0.0" nodeRatioX="0.0" nodeRatioY="0.0" offsetX="0.0" offsetY="0.0" upX="0.0" upY="-1.0"/></y:ModelParameter></y:NodeLabel>
        </y:GenericNode>
      </data>
    </node>
    <node id="n57">
      <data key="d5"/>
      <data key="d6">
        <y:GenericNode configuration="com.yworks.flowchart.process">
          <y:Geometry height="357.22666666666646" width="348.26666666666597" x="-2565.932819010417" y="637.4155208333332"/>
          <y:Fill color="#E8EEF7" color2="#FF9900" transparent="false"/>
          <y:BorderStyle color="#000000" type="line" width="1.0"/>
          <y:NodeLabel alignment="left" autoSizePolicy="content" fontFamily="Dialog" fontSize="12" fontStyle="plain" hasBackgroundColor="false" hasLineColor="false" height="327.42578125" horizontalTextPosition="center" iconTextGap="4" modelName="custom" textColor="#000000" verticalTextPosition="bottom" visible="true" width="300.1796875" x="24.043489583332757" xml:space="preserve" y="14.90044270833323">This is a minimalistic model for the ADI system,
where ADAS capabilities using complex sensors 
like cameras, radar and lidar are not made part
of the ADI system. This is done on purpose to
enable a cost effective and base vehicle 
configuration level cost to the resulting system.

Because of this approach, the steering wheel angle 
is not made a part of the driver intention detection.

We beleive, a hostile driver intention can be detected
solely based on the following input cues:

- flow of the driver acceleration requests
- geolocation to narrow down locations of interest

Further the system can be supported with additional 
input cues from low-cost systems that are ubiquitiously
available including economy class road vehicles.

Sensor spoofing for steering wheel sensors needs to be
considered in the TARA analysis.<y:LabelModel><y:SmartNodeLabelModel distance="4.0"/></y:LabelModel><y:ModelParameter><y:SmartNodeLabelModelParameter labelRatioX="0.0" labelRatioY="0.0" nodeRatioX="0.0" nodeRatioY="0.0" offsetX="0.0" offsetY="0.0" upX="0.0" upY="-1.0"/></y:ModelParameter></y:NodeLabel>
        </y:GenericNode>
      </data>
    </node>
    <node id="n58">
      <data key="d5"/>
      <data key="d6">
        <y:GenericNode configuration="com.yworks.flowchart.process">
          <y:Geometry height="163.0" width="381.546875" x="-2998.4471549479167" y="688.9370703124991"/>
          <y:Fill color="#E8EEF7" color2="#FF9900" transparent="false"/>
          <y:BorderStyle color="#000000" type="line" width="1.0"/>
          <y:NodeLabel alignment="left" autoSizePolicy="content" fontFamily="Dialog" fontSize="12" fontStyle="plain" hasBackgroundColor="false" hasLineColor="false" height="151.01171875" horizontalTextPosition="center" iconTextGap="4" modelName="custom" textColor="#000000" verticalTextPosition="bottom" visible="true" width="361.486328125" x="10.0302734375" xml:space="preserve" y="5.994140625">In general, driver emotional state can be estimated more precisely 
by a camera based driver monitoring system compared to a simple 
capacitive resistive sensor on the steering wheel. 

However for a hostile driver can easily disable a camera based 
driver monitoring system using a sticker.

Furthermore, use of simpler, cheaper sensors make the resulting
system more accessible and a better candidate for a standard 
feature in all cars, irrespective of the price tag.<y:LabelModel><y:SmartNodeLabelModel distance="4.0"/></y:LabelModel><y:ModelParameter><y:SmartNodeLabelModelParameter labelRatioX="0.0" labelRatioY="0.0" nodeRatioX="0.0" nodeRatioY="0.0" offsetX="0.0" offsetY="0.0" upX="0.0" upY="-1.0"/></y:ModelParameter></y:NodeLabel>
        </y:GenericNode>
      </data>
    </node>
    <node id="n59">
      <data key="d5"/>
      <data key="d6">
        <y:GenericNode configuration="com.yworks.flowchart.process">
          <y:Geometry height="230.2699999999998" width="504.328125" x="-2636.2149511718753" y="307.10302083333306"/>
          <y:Fill color="#E8EEF7" color2="#FF9900" transparent="false"/>
          <y:BorderStyle color="#000000" type="line" width="1.0"/>
          <y:NodeLabel alignment="left" autoSizePolicy="content" fontFamily="Dialog" fontSize="12" fontStyle="plain" hasBackgroundColor="false" hasLineColor="false" height="195.115234375" horizontalTextPosition="center" iconTextGap="4" modelName="custom" textColor="#000000" verticalTextPosition="bottom" visible="true" width="492.197265625" x="6.0654296875" xml:space="preserve" y="17.577382812499877">GNSS systems can be prone to drifts and insufficient precision.

However GNSS location to set the alertness level may not need to;
be as precise as it would be necessary to feed a automated driving task.

TODO improve (and check whether this measure is in conflict with the amok detection task):
The real time kinematics can be used to conservatively plausibilize the raw GNSS signals 
against the speed profile from the HD Map and immediate neighbourhood of the reported 
geolocation. Real time kinematics can also counteract GNSS Spoofing with replay.

Maybe the hardest requirement of the ADI system is on the precision of the GNSS system.

GNSS Spoofing must be considered in the TARA analysis.<y:LabelModel><y:SmartNodeLabelModel distance="4.0"/></y:LabelModel><y:ModelParameter><y:SmartNodeLabelModelParameter labelRatioX="0.0" labelRatioY="0.0" nodeRatioX="0.0" nodeRatioY="0.0" offsetX="0.0" offsetY="0.0" upX="0.0" upY="-1.0"/></y:ModelParameter></y:NodeLabel>
        </y:GenericNode>
      </data>
    </node>
